<TITLE> Father, child killed by elephants in Bandarban </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bandarban, Dec 14 (bdnews24.com)  Wild elephants trampled a four-year-old boy and his father in Bandarban on Monday. The deceased were identified as Abul Kashem, 38, and his son Md Rashed of Noapara village of Lama upazila. Lama police chief Mohammad Hossain told bdnews24.com some wild elephants came out from the hills and attacked Kashem's house. The police later recovered those bodies from the spot and sent them to Bandarban Hospital for post-mortem, he said. The elephants also rampaged through some houses on their way back. bdnews24
